# ========================================
TC-AMS-REJECT-01

SUMMARY
AMS R1 - Advisor/Farmer Successfully Rejects AMS Finding with Valid Reason

DESCRIPTION
Verifies the complete successful Reject journey for an Advisor/Agent or Farmer responding to an AMS Round 1 Red finding. The test covers the full flow from login through to the AMS Respond to Findings screen. It verifies the red warning message at the top of the screen, the quick filters (View all, Action Required), all required column headers in the findings table, the red parcel symbol indicating response required, the View Map action icon on each row, and the AMS status legend at the bottom left. The test then selects a parcel for rejection, verifies the side drawer content (bold Edit parcel header, Townland, Parcel No, red missing mandatory information message, Do you accept/reject findings question), selects Reject, verifies all five reject reason options, saves successfully and verifies the green toast message. It also verifies the red symbol is removed from the parcel after responding, the Submit button behaviour when not all parcels are responded to, the red warning when attempting to submit with outstanding responses, and the Other free text option which is mandatory and capped at 300 characters.

STEPS

Action	Data	Expected Result
If Agent: Log in to BISS with agent credentials and OTP. If Farmer: Log in with farmer credentials and OTP	Agent username and password from INET query. OTP/PIN	Successfully authenticated and landed on BISS Home page
If Agent: Navigate to Agent Tools and select AMS then select the client herd. If Farmer: Navigate to Farmer Dashboard directly	Herd number from VWBS_AMS_NOTIFIED_HERD query	Farmer Dashboard displayed with AMS Findings panel visible
Click Respond to Findings button on the AMS Findings panel		AMS Respond to Findings screen displayed
Verify red warning message at the top of the screen		Red warning message reads: Actions and/or failure to take action in response to AMS Notifications may impact all area based scheme payments. Please respond below
Verify quick filters at the top of the findings list		View all and Action Required filter buttons are visible
Verify column headers in the findings table		Columns present in order: (1) Red exclamation/green tick no header (2) Townland (3) Parcel no./Plot ref. (4) AMS status (5) AMS findings (6) Accept/Reject findings? (7) Claimed area (ha) (8) Parcel use (9) Action view map icon
Verify the parcels listed in the findings table		Only Round 1 Red parcels are displayed in the list
Verify the AMS findings column content		AMS findings column is populated with Artificial Surface for the relevant parcels
Verify the red symbol on each parcel row		Each parcel with a pending response shows a red symbol indicating response required
Verify the Action column on each parcel row		A View Map icon is present at the end of each parcel row
Verify the AMS status legend at the bottom left of the screen		AMS status legend displayed showing Red Non Compliant
Click on a Red parcel row to open the side drawer	Parcel number from vwbs_error_land query	Side drawer opens for the selected parcel
Verify the side drawer header		Edit parcel displayed in bold at the top of the side drawer styled as per Figma
Verify parcel navigation in the side drawer		Townland and Parcel No./Plot Ref. displayed with ability to navigate between parcels
Verify the red symbol at the top of the side drawer		Red symbol displayed with message missing mandatory information
Verify the question displayed in the side drawer		Question reads: Do you accept/reject findings?
Select Reject		Reject option selected
Verify the reject reason prompt		Message displayed: Give a reason why you reject Area Monitoring findings?
Verify the reject reason options displayed		The following options are visible: Bare soil, Crop is as claimed, Feature no longer exists, Temporary bale storage, Other
Select a reason other than Other for example Bare soil		Reason selected successfully
Click Save Changes		Green toast message displayed: You have successfully updated details for Parcel No X
Close the side drawer		Side drawer closes and user is returned to the AMS screen
Verify the red symbol on the responded parcel		The red symbol on the left side of the parcel row is no longer shown
Do NOT submit - verify Submit button is present when not all parcels responded to		Submit button is visible when responses are outstanding
Attempt to submit with parcels that have not been responded to		Red warning message displayed indicating not all parcels have been responded to
Open side drawer on another Red parcel select Reject and select Other as the reject reason		Free text box appears below Other option - it is mandatory and accepts a maximum of 300 characters
Attempt to click Save Changes with the Other free text box left empty		Save is blocked - free text is required when Other is selected
Enter valid text in the free text box up to 300 characters and click Save Changes		Green toast message: You have successfully updated details for Parcel No X

# ========================================
TC-AMS-REJECT-02

SUMMARY
AMS R1 - Save Changes Without Selecting Reject Reason Triggers Validation Error

DESCRIPTION
Verifies that when a user selects Reject for an AMS Round 1 finding but clicks Save Changes without selecting a reject reason, the system correctly blocks the save and displays validation errors. The radio buttons beside the reject reason options must turn red to indicate a selection is required, and a reason required message must appear in red. This is a mandatory field validation test confirming the reject flow cannot be completed without a reason being provided. After the validation error the user selects a valid reason and saves - the system must show the green toast confirmation.

STEPS

Action	Data	Expected Result
Complete login and navigate to the AMS Respond to Findings screen following TC-AMS-REJECT-01 Steps 1 to 3	Same herd and agent login as TC-AMS-REJECT-01	AMS Respond to Findings screen displayed
Click on a Red parcel row to open the side drawer	Parcel number from vwbs_error_land query	Side drawer opens
Verify the red symbol at the top of the side drawer		Red symbol with message missing mandatory information displayed
Verify the question displayed in the side drawer		Do you accept/reject findings? shown
Select Reject		Reject option selected
Verify the reject reason prompt is displayed		Give a reason why you reject Area Monitoring findings? displayed
Verify all reject reason options are visible		The following options displayed: Bare soil, Crop is as claimed, Feature no longer exists, Temporary bale storage, Crop is as claimed, Other
Do NOT select any reject reason		No reason selected - all radio buttons remain unselected
Click Save Changes		Save is blocked - validation is triggered
Verify radio button validation styling		Radio buttons beside all reject reason options turn red
Verify validation message		reason required message displayed in red
Select a valid reason for example Crop is as claimed		Reason selected and red validation styling clears
Click Save Changes		Green toast displayed: You have successfully updated details for Parcel No X
Close the side drawer		Side drawer closes and user is returned to the AMS screen